window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

Method: GET
Route: /api/docs/swagger-ui-init.js
Payload: {}
Response: 
window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

Method: GET
Route: /api/docs/swagger-ui-init.js
Payload: {}
Response: 
window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

Route: /api/docs/swagger-ui-init.js
Payload: {}
Response: 
window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

Timestamp: 3/3/2024, 8:14:13 PM
Method: GET
Route: /api/docs/swagger-ui-init.js
Payload: {}
Response: 
window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",

      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",

      }

};

  // Build a system

  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;

      const pid = setInterval(() => {

        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

Timestamp: 3/3/2024, 8:14:23 PM
Method: GET
Route: /api/docs/swagger-ui-init.js
Payload: {}
Response: 
window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

  if (url && url.length > 1) {

  } else {

  }

  "swaggerDoc": {

  // Build a system

  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;

      const pid = setInterval(() => {

        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

Method: GET
Route: /api/docs/swagger-ui-init.js
Payload: {}
Response: 
window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

  if (url && url.length > 1) {

  } else {

  }

  "swaggerDoc": {

  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;

      const pid = setInterval(() => {

      }, 500)

    }
  }

    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui

Method: GET
Route: /api/docs/swagger-ui-init.js
Payload: {}
Response: 
window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

  if (url && url.length > 1) {

  } else {

  }

  "swaggerDoc": {

  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;

      const pid = setInterval(() => {

        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

Timestamp: 3/3/2024, 8:14:50 PM
Method: GET
Route: /api/docs/swagger-ui-init.js
Payload: {}
Response: 
window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

  if (url && url.length > 1) {

  } else {

  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {

};

  // Build a system

  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;

      const pid = setInterval(() => {

      }, 500)

    }
  }

    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui

Timestamp: 3/3/2024, 8:15:06 PM
Method: GET
Route: /api/docs/swagger-ui-init.js
Payload: {}
Response: 
window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",

      }

  },

};

  // Build a system

  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

Timestamp: 3/3/2024, 8:15:15 PM
Method: GET
Route: /api/docs/swagger-ui-init.js
Payload: {}
Response: 
window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",

      }
    ],

    "tags": []
  },

};

  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

  if (url && url.length > 1) {

  } else {

  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {

Method: GET
Route: /api/docs/swagger-ui-init.js
Payload: {}
Response: 
window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

  if (url && url.length > 1) {

  } else {

  }

  // Build a system

  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc

    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;

      }, 500)

    }
  }

    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui

Timestamp: 3/3/2024, 8:16:47 PM
Method: GET
Route: /api/docs/swagger-ui-init.js
Payload: {}
Response: 
window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

  // Build a system

  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;

      const pid = setInterval(() => {

        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

Timestamp: 3/3/2024, 8:16:57 PM
Method: GET
Route: /api/docs/swagger-ui-init.js
Payload: {}
Response: 
window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;

      const pid = setInterval(() => {

      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

Timestamp: 3/3/2024, 8:17:10 PM
Method: GET
Route: /api/docs/swagger-ui-init.js
Payload: {}
Response: 
window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {

  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {

      }

  // Build a system

  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;
    const value = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.apiKeyValue;
    if (!!key && !!value) {
      const pid = setInterval(() => {
        const authorized = ui.preauthorizeApiKey(key, value);
        if(!!authorized) clearInterval(pid);
      }, 500)

    }
  }

  if (customOptions.authAction) {
    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
}

window.onload = function() {
  // Build a system
  var url = window.location.search.match(/url=([^&]+)/);
  if (url && url.length > 1) {
    url = decodeURIComponent(url[1]);
  } else {
    url = window.location.origin;
  }
  var options = {
  "swaggerDoc": {
    "openapi": "3.1.0",
    "info": {
      "title": "Docker Blog Express API",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "license": {
        "name": "MIT",
        "url": "https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.html"
      },
      "contact": {
        "name": "Angel Herrarte",
        "email": "angelherrarte3@gmail.com"
      }
    },
    "servers": [
      {
        "url": "http://localhost:3000"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {},
    "components": {},
    "tags": []
  },
  "customOptions": {}
};
  url = options.swaggerUrl || url
  var urls = options.swaggerUrls
  var customOptions = options.customOptions
  var spec1 = options.swaggerDoc
  var swaggerOptions = {
    spec: spec1,
    url: url,
    urls: urls,
    dom_id: '#swagger-ui',
    deepLinking: true,
    presets: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.presets.apis,
      SwaggerUIStandalonePreset
    ],
    plugins: [
      SwaggerUIBundle.plugins.DownloadUrl
    ],
    layout: "StandaloneLayout"
  }
  for (var attrname in customOptions) {
    swaggerOptions[attrname] = customOptions[attrname];
  }
  var ui = SwaggerUIBundle(swaggerOptions)

  if (customOptions.oauth) {
    ui.initOAuth(customOptions.oauth)
  }

  if (customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey) {
    const key = customOptions.preauthorizeApiKey.authDefinitionKey;

      const pid = setInterval(() => {

      }, 500)

    }
  }

    ui.authActions.authorize(customOptions.authAction)
  }

  window.ui = ui
